---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
---

<Base title="About" description="About Neuman Learn — free, open-source programming education.">
  <section class="py-24 px-6">
    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto">
      <h1
        class="text-4xl sm:text-5xl font-bold tracking-tight mb-8"
        style="color: var(--color-text);"
      >
        About
      </h1>

      <div class="space-y-6 text-base leading-relaxed" style="color: var(--color-text-muted);">
        <p>
          Neuman Learn is a collection of free, open-source programming courses built around one idea:
          <strong style="color: var(--color-text);">you learn to code by writing code.</strong>
        </p>

        <p>
          Every course is structured as a progression of hands-on projects. No video lectures, no
          multiple-choice quizzes, no simulated environments. You write real code in a real editor,
          run real tests, and build real things.
        </p>

        <h2
          class="text-2xl font-bold pt-4"
          style="color: var(--color-text);"
        >
          Philosophy
        </h2>

        <p>
          Most programming education optimizes for completion rates. We optimize for capability.
          The difference matters: completion means you watched all the videos. Capability means
          you can build software.
        </p>

        <p>
          Each project in our courses includes a clear problem statement, a test suite to verify
          your implementation, and an annotated solution walkthrough for when you get stuck. The
          tests don't just check output — they verify that your code handles edge cases, follows
          best practices, and actually solves the problem.
        </p>

        <h2
          class="text-2xl font-bold pt-4"
          style="color: var(--color-text);"
        >
          Open Source
        </h2>

        <p>
          All course content is MIT-licensed and hosted on GitHub. You can fork any course, modify
          it for your needs, contribute improvements, or use it to teach others. Quality programming
          education should not be locked behind paywalls.
        </p>

        <p>
          Contributions are welcome — whether it's fixing a typo, improving a test case, adding
          a new project, or translating content to another language.
        </p>

        <h2
          class="text-2xl font-bold pt-4"
          style="color: var(--color-text);"
        >
          Built by
        </h2>

        <p>
          Neuman Learn is created by
          <a
            href="https://travisjneuman.com"
            target="_blank"
            rel="noopener noreferrer"
          >
            Travis Neuman
          </a>, a software engineer who believes the best way to learn is to build.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Base>
